      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "Concept ACK. I think chaining commands together without intermediate error checking like this is definitely dangerous and poor practice, but there are probably legitimate use-cases for testing, etc.\r\n\r\nThinking out loud: verbosity is a very common option for RPCs. Perhaps we should consider making it a query string in the URL rather than adding parameters to every RPC that requires it. Maybe that's not practical, but worth considering.",
